15 Customization
****************

15.1 Basic Configuration
========================

     (use-package simply-annotate
       :ensure t
       :custom
       ;; Choose display style
       (simply-annotate-display-style '(highlight fringe)) ; single or combined styles

       ;; Customize the highlight face
       (simply-annotate-highlight-face '(:background "lightblue" :foreground "darkblue"))

       ;; Customize storage location
       (simply-annotate-file "~/my-annotations.el")

       ;; Customize annotation buffer height
       (simply-annotate-buffer-height 0.25)

       ;; Annotation level settings
       (simply-annotate-default-level 'defun)  ; 'file, 'defun, or 'line

       ;; Fringe indicator settings
       (simply-annotate-fringe-indicator 'right-triangle)
       (simply-annotate-fringe-face 'simply-annotate-fringe-face)

       :bind
       ("C-c A" . simply-annotate-mode))

15.2 Threading and Collaboration Configuration
==============================================

Configure team collaboration and threading features:

     (use-package simply-annotate
       :custom
       ;; Author configuration
       (simply-annotate-author-list '("John Doe" "Jane Smith" "Bob Wilson" "Alice Chen"))
       (simply-annotate-prompt-for-author 'threads-only)  ; Prompt only for replies
       (simply-annotate-remember-author-per-file t)       ; Remember per file

       ;; Customize available statuses and priorities
       (simply-annotate-thread-statuses '("open" "in-progress" "resolved" "closed"))
       (simply-annotate-priority-levels '("low" "normal" "high" "critical"))

       :bind
       ("C-c A" . simply-annotate-mode)
       ("C-c 0" . simply-annotate-show-all)
       ("C-c 9" . simply-annotate-jump-to-file))

15.3 Configuration Examples
===========================

15.3.1 Single User (Default)
----------------------------

     ;; Minimal setup - works like original simply-annotate
     (setq simply-annotate-prompt-for-author nil)

15.3.2 Code Review Team
-----------------------

     ;; Review team setup
     (setq simply-annotate-author-list '("John Reviewer" "Jane Developer" "Bob QA"))
     (setq simply-annotate-prompt-for-author 'threads-only)  ; Prompt for replies only
     (setq simply-annotate-remember-author-per-file t)       ; Different authors per file

15.3.3 Multi-Project Consultant
-------------------------------

     ;; Different clients/contexts
     (setq simply-annotate-author-list '("John (Client A)" "John (Client B)" "John (Internal)"))
     (setq simply-annotate-prompt-for-author 'first-only)    ; Prompt once per session
     (setq simply-annotate-remember-author-per-file t)       ; Remember per project

15.3.4 Project-Aware Setup
--------------------------

     ;; Per-project databases (committable to version control)
     (setq simply-annotate-database-strategy 'project)

     ;; Or merge project and global
     (setq simply-annotate-database-strategy 'both)

15.4 Core Customization Variables
=================================

‘simply-annotate-file’
     File to store annotations in global mode.  Default:
     ‘~/.emacs.d/simply-annotations.el’

‘simply-annotate-database-strategy’
     Where to store annotations.  ‘global’ (single file), ‘project’
     (per-project file at project root), or ‘both’ (merge project and
     global).  Default: ‘global’

‘simply-annotate-project-file’
     Filename for per-project annotation databases, placed at the
     project root.  Default: ‘.simply-annotations.el’

‘simply-annotate-highlight-face’
     Face for highlighted annotated text.  Default: ‘'(:inherit
     highlight)’

‘simply-annotate-buffer-name’
     Name of the annotation display buffer.  Default: ‘"*Annotation*"’

‘simply-annotate-buffer-height’
     Height of annotation buffer as fraction of frame height.  Default:
     ‘0.3’

‘simply-annotate-display-style’
     How to display annotations.  A single symbol or list of symbols.
     Options: ‘'highlight’, ‘'tint’, ‘'fringe’, ‘'fringe-bracket’,
     ‘'subtle’.  Default: ‘'fringe’

‘simply-annotate-fringe-indicator’
     Symbol for fringe indicators.  Options: ‘'left-triangle’,
     ‘'right-triangle’, ‘'filled-rectangle’, ‘'custom’.  Default:
     ‘'right-triangle’

‘simply-annotate-fringe-face’
     Face for fringe indicators.  Default:
     ‘'simply-annotate-fringe-face’

‘simply-annotate-inline-position’
     Where to display inline blocks relative to the annotated region.
     Options: ‘'after’, ‘'above’.  Default: ‘'after’

‘simply-annotate-inline-max-lines’
     Maximum number of lines shown for inline annotations.  Lines beyond
     this limit are truncated with a count.  Set to ‘nil’ to show all
     lines.  Default: ‘20’

‘simply-annotate-inline-pointer-after’
     Pointer string shown between annotated text and the inline box
     below.  Supports multiline strings (use ‘\n’).  Set to ‘nil’ to
     disable.  Default: ‘"▴"’

‘simply-annotate-inline-pointer-above’
     Pointer string shown between the inline box above and annotated
     text.  Supports multiline strings (use ‘\n’).  Set to ‘nil’ to
     disable.  Default: ‘"▾"’

‘simply-annotate-stale-face’
     Face used for stale annotation markers.  Default: tomato
     foreground, italic.

15.5 Annotation Level Variables
===============================

‘simply-annotate-levels’
     List of available annotation levels.  Default: ‘'(file defun line)’

‘simply-annotate-default-level’
     Default level for new annotations and for existing annotations that
     lack a level tag.  Default: ‘'defun’

15.6 Threading and Collaboration Variables
==========================================

‘simply-annotate-author-list’
     List of available authors for annotations.  Default: ‘(list
     user-full-name)’

‘simply-annotate-prompt-for-author’
     When to prompt for author selection.  Options: ‘nil’,
     ‘'first-only’, ‘'always’, ‘'threads-only’.  Default: ‘nil’

‘simply-annotate-remember-author-per-file’
     Whether to remember author choice per file.  Default: ‘nil’

‘simply-annotate-thread-statuses’
     Available status values for annotation threads.  Default: ‘'("open"
     "in-progress" "resolved" "closed")’

‘simply-annotate-priority-levels’
     Available priority levels for annotations.  Default: ‘'("low"
     "normal" "high" "critical")’

15.7 Custom Faces
=================

     ;; Custom highlight face for annotations
     (defface my-annotation-face
       '((t :background "lightyellow" :foreground "black"))
       "Face for annotation highlights")

     (setq simply-annotate-highlight-face 'my-annotation-face)

     ;; Custom fringe face
     (defface my-fringe-face
       '((t :foreground "red" :background nil))
       "Face for fringe annotation indicators")

     (setq simply-annotate-fringe-face 'my-fringe-face)

15.8 Display Style Configuration
================================

     ;; Use only fringe indicators (minimal visual impact)
     (setq simply-annotate-display-style 'fringe)

     ;; Use fringe brackets spanning the annotated region
     (setq simply-annotate-display-style 'fringe-bracket)

     ;; Use a subtle background tint (adapts to current theme)
     (setq simply-annotate-display-style 'tint)

     ;; Use traditional highlighting
     (setq simply-annotate-display-style 'highlight)

     ;; Combine styles as a list
     (setq simply-annotate-display-style '(highlight fringe))
     (setq simply-annotate-display-style '(tint fringe-bracket))

     ;; Customize fringe indicators
     (setq simply-annotate-fringe-indicator 'left-triangle)

15.9 Advanced Customization
===========================

15.9.1 Custom Fringe Bitmaps
----------------------------

You can define custom fringe bitmaps:

     (when (fboundp 'define-fringe-bitmap)
       (define-fringe-bitmap 'my-annotation-bitmap
         [#b00000000
          #b00011000
          #b00111100
          #b01111110
          #b11111111
          #b01111110
          #b00111100
          #b00011000]
         nil nil 'center))

     (setq simply-annotate-fringe-indicator 'custom)

15.9.2 Global Mode Setup
------------------------

To enable annotation mode automatically:

     (use-package simply-annotate
       :hook
       (find-file-hook . simply-annotate-mode)
       :bind
       ("C-c A" . simply-annotate-mode)
       ("C-c 0" . simply-annotate-show-all)
       ("C-c 9" . simply-annotate-jump-to-file))


